# YIELD.md Validation Criteria

This file defines what YIELD.md must contain. Used by QA to validate.

## Required Sections

- [ ] Header with purpose statement
- [ ] Yield types table with ALL types listed
- [ ] Format examples for EACH yield type

## Required Yield Types (must all be documented)

- [ ] `complete`
- [ ] `need-user-input`
- [ ] `need-context`
- [ ] `need-decision`
- [ ] `need-agent`
- [ ] `blocked`
- [ ] `approved`
- [ ] `improvement-request`
- [ ] `escalate-phase`
- [ ] `escalate-user`
- [ ] `error`

## Required Format Examples

Each yield type must have a TOML example showing:
- [ ] `[yield]` section with `type` field
- [ ] Type-specific payload fields
- [ ] `[context]` section for state serialization (where applicable)

## Required Content

- [ ] Payload field documentation per type
- [ ] Context serialization format
- [ ] Reference to orchestration-system.md Section 3
- [ ] Difference between producer and QA yield types

## Validation Command

```bash
# Check all yield types are documented
grep -E "^### .*(complete|need-user-input|need-context|blocked|approved|improvement-request|escalate-phase)" skills/shared/YIELD.md

# Check TOML examples exist
grep -c '```toml' skills/shared/YIELD.md  # Should be >= 8
```
